Advantages:
- removes code duplication 
- code is easily extensible and scalable 
- can change the strategy at run time 

Disadvantages:
- Increases the number of classes ( many more of strategy )
- can be a overkill for simple problems ( if there are only one or two behaviours this is just a overkill in that case )

When not to use it:
- when the behaviour of the child or the objects are not gonna change and the behaviours are not expected to grow, then adding this would simply increase complexity 
- if the extra abstraction is creating complexity rather than real benifit, we should not be using this pattern 

